hopobject.body: Best Site good looking kroger pharmacy locations near me Makeup artist Rick Baker did it again with "The Nutty Professor," earning himself an Academy Award for his incredible job transforming Eddie Murphy into Sherman Klump, a well as his entire family in sequel, "The Klumps." Murphy essentially disappears under the mountain of chins, cheeks and rolls. For the first "Nutty," Baker sketch-sculpted over a mask of Eddie's face. Baker then turned it into a latex mold that contoured to the actor's face. To play the 300 lb. professor, Murphy wore a fat suit made of polyurethane foam covered in spandex. Latex bladders filled with water were used to make the fat suit jiggle. Murphy also donned oversized rubber hands.
